# Festag light glass surfaces

In **light mode**, neutral content containers use a frosted glass look (not opaque Apple gray fills).

## Tokens

```css
--festag-glass-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.58);
--festag-glass-bg-strong: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
--festag-glass-bg-soft: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.42);
--festag-glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
--festag-glass-edge: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06);
--festag-glass-blur: blur(18px) saturate(155%);
--festag-glass-shadow: /* inset highlight + soft lift */;
--festag-glass-shadow-soft: /* lighter variant */;
```

Recipe for a glass container:

```css
background: var(--festag-glass-bg);
border: 1px solid var(--festag-glass-border);
box-shadow: var(--festag-glass-shadow-soft);
backdrop-filter: var(--festag-glass-blur);
-webkit-backdrop-filter: var(--festag-glass-blur);
border-radius: 20px–28px;
```

Utility class: `.festag-glass`

For executive/status tiles:

```css
--st-ex-surface: var(--festag-glass-bg-soft);
--st-ex-surface-hover: var(--festag-glass-bg);
```

## When to use

- Floating portal main panel (`.portal-app-main`)
- Horizontal card tiles (Projektbericht, Projektprognose, executive overview boxes)
- Informational capsules / caption tiles on the gray canvas
- Nested cards that sit inside the portal shell

## Do not use

- Opaque `#f5f5f7` / `#ffffff` for these light-mode containers when glass is intended
- Glass blur on dark canvas — keep OLED hierarchy from AGENTS.md
- Glass on print/PDF document surfaces (invoices stay solid white)

## Dark mode

On `html[data-theme="dark"]` / `classic-dark`, do not force light glass. Use:

- Canvas: `--festag-black-canvas` / `#000000`
- Content: `--festag-black-content` / `#0c0c0e`–`#111114`
- Soft fills: `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06)` etc.
